@Kaffie well being a capitalist myself, I really can't argue with you there. I do hope you can see some of the positive features of these systems. and I mean that in a "relative" sense. personally, I'm "mostly" encouraged by the new levels of transparency that are now possible solely due to the introduction of these blockchains and their use in previously proprietary systems. 

I've long since distanced myself from Bitcoin (for personal reasons), but I'm very active in the Ethereum community. There are tremendous things that can be done today with smart contracts, with more "meaningful" use-cases arriving almost daily.

Anyway, these systems are far from what I would consider perfect (if there is such a thing), but I welcome the improvements that they do bring to a mostly broken system that just frustrates me. I also welcome your perspective as it helps balance my own.

@krixano does 0Play Chat support "@" mentions that will show up in the Newsfeed? There is a "Following" button, but I don't know what it does. 

I'm expecting to offer app notifications with 0Explorer, but I'm still looking for something better on desktop (specifically Mac); **I'd be happy with even just a COUNTER BADGE in the browser title to display how many mentions are unread.** Anything I can do to help facilitate this will be my pleasure to support.

**EDIT:** ok, I see the chat in the Newsfeed; probably should have checked that first lol. But does it support mentions as well? I'm not 100% on how mentions are queried by the database (must you prefix with the "@" symbol, or will it match any txt containing your user_id?) thanks!
